The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs), which are a fundamental topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for solving CSPs. The use of forbidden patterns and counting and quantification over variables and values suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves optimization and tractability analysis, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
